<TEXT>
<P>
 The Leopard Man (AMC Monday at 8:30 a.m. and 5:30 p.m.) is notable as one of 
producer Val Lewton's fabled '40s horror pictures. Directed by Jacques 
Tourneur, it deals with a mysterious series of murders in a New Mexico town. 
</P>
<P>
 AMC Monday Gorilla Fest: The 1933 King Kong (at 9:30 a.m. and 8:05 p.m.), The 
Son of Kong (at 11:15 a.m. and 10 p.m.) and Mighty Joe Young (at noon and 11:30 
p.m.). 
</P>
