<TEXT>
<P>
 LIFE WITH AN ELECTRIC CAR by Noel Perrin (Sierra Club Books: $12; 217 pp.) . 
When a student asked ecology professor Noel Perrin why he a drove gas-guzzling 
truck, he began to look for an electric car. He finally found one in 
California, but its limited cruising range and inability to climb steep hills 
complicated the trip home to Vermont. Perrin blends serious discussions of 
pollution with a personal account of his travels. His endearing, avuncular 
approach to questions of energy use will probably win more converts to the 
environmental cause than the confrontational stance of many authors who 
champion the movement. 
</P>
