<TEXT>
<P>
 ALIAS OLYMPIA: A Woman's Search for Manet's Notorious Model and Her Own Desire 
by Eunice Lipton (Meridian: $9.95; 181 pp.) . Art historian Eunice Lipton 
recounts her fascination with the elusive Victorine Meurent, the model who 
posed for "Olympia," "Le Dejeuner sur l'herbe" and other celebrated paintings 
by Manet. In an intriguing example of historical detective work, Lipton 
reconstructs Meurent's life from a scant array of documents and references. But 
the author seems to identify a little too strongly with her subject and builds 
a portrait of her as a painter without having seen a single canvas. 
