</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MISSISSIPPI HISTORY by Steve Yarbrough (University of Missouri Press: $14.95; 
156 pp., paperback original). Blighted hopes hang in the humid air of 
Yarbrough's fictional Delta town of Indianola: In these stories men and women 
who hoped to make something of themselves watch their dreams fade into 
mediocrity. The narrators of "Hoe Hands" and "Hazel Baker" attain some insight 
into their lives, but they lack the resolution to act on it. The tantalizing 
memories of the potential they once had dogs the characters' steps, making it 
harder to trudge to work each morning. 
</P>
