<BYLINE>
<P>
By Sandy Masuo 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Megadeth, "Youthanasia," Capitol. Megadeth main man Dave Mustaine has a 
horde of demons to wrestle.Fueled by a fiery intellect and fierce instrumental 
support, his musical exorcisms are as enticing as they are grim. "Youthanasia" 
seethes with the usual pungent guitar, strafing riffage and relentless rhythms 
infused with a covert melodiousness. Mustaine's vocals seem earthier, which 
enhances his forbidding commentaries about society's (and his own) fatal flaws. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Sandy Masuo 
