<TEXT>
<P>
 * 1/2 Various artists, "The Glory of Gershwin," Mercury. If you always wanted 
to hear Jon Bon Jovi jam on George Gershwin, then: a) this is the album for 
you; and b) you are one sick puppy.A few guests -- Elvis Costello, Kate Bush, 
Peter Gabriel, Robert Palmer -- do some justice to the great composer on this 
17-track tribute, which is also a collaboration with 80-year-old harmonica 
player Larry Adler. But producer George Martin has little imagination about how 
to merge his guests' gifts with Gershwin's. New albums are rated on a scale of 
one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars (good) and four stars 
(excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Chris Willman 
