<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO REWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Very Very Nick at Nite (Sunday at 8:30 p.m. on Nickelodeon) features four 
episodes of "I Love Lucy" in which Lucy tries to get herself out of a jam by 
donning a disguise. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick at Nite celebrates Halloween with A Bewitched Halloween (Monday at 8 
p.m.), featuring four episodes of the classic '60s supernatural sitcom. 
</P>
<P>
 Cliff Gorman and Mel Ferrer star in a Police Story (Wednesday at 3 p.m. on 
A&E) about a tough cop who tracks down a rapist-child molester who always prays 
for his victims. 
</P>
<P>
 The staff at WJM is shocked when Mary starts dating Murray's father (Lew 
Ayres) on The Mary Tyler Moore Show (Wednesday at 10 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Angie Dickinson and Bert Convy guest on Police Story (Thursday at 3 p.m. on 
A&E) in an episode in which a female officer is sent to vice squad. 
</P>
<P>
 Danny Thomas guests as a thumbless alien with an eye in the back of his head 
on the famous "It May Look Like a Walnut" episode of The Dick Van Dyke Show 
(Thursday at 11 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Get out your handkerchiefs. Nick at Nite is repeating the final episode of The 
Mary Tyler Moore Show (Friday at 10:30 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
