<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE LOW COST OF PEP IN THE MID '40S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "The Price of Pep" (Oct. 6) reminded me of my days as head song leader at 
Woodrow Wilson High School in Long Beach in the mid '40s. 
</P>
<P>
 In that era, our mothers made our outfits from heavy white cotton -- with high 
necks, long sleeves, and skirts to the knee. 
</P>
<P>
 We wore a crimson and gold letterman's "W" on our chests and white shoes with 
bobby socks. Our pompons were constructed of cut-off broom handles with red and 
yellow crepe-paper twists. 
</P>
<P>
 How modest (and inexpensive) our costumes were in those days. 
</P>
<P>
 PAULINE NELSON COWLE 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Palisades 
</P>
</TEXT>
