<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADVICE THAT MAKES IT EASY TO SWALLOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "A Bitter Pill to Swallow" in C.A. Wedlan's "Health Roundup" (Oct. 18): 
Because I must consume "big, chalky horse pills," (calcium), I can suggest a 
method that helps. 
</P>
<P>
 Generally, people will throw their heads back, closing the throat too soon. 
Tilting the head forward and placing the pill on the tongue facilitates 
swallowing the pill with a large sip of water. It works. 
</P>
<P>
 BARBARA TABLER 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara 
</P>
</TEXT>
