<P>
GERMAN ELECTION RESULTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your news analysis of the German election ("Kohl's Real Challenge Comes After 
Election Win," Oct. 18) has completely ignored the most important news of the 
event, namely that the right-wing Republican Party is now down to a mere 1.9% 
of the national popular vote. 
</P>
<P>
 With all the time and space you have spent over the years, warning and 
predicting that the danger of a repeat of 1933 should be taken seriously, 
because of the comparatively few racial incidents recently, the fact of the 
decline of the right in elections should not have been missed. 
</P>
