<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOUGH GUN CONTROL LAWS TO BE DRAFTED IN CANADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuter 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canada's Justice Minister vowed Friday to increase gun control and to present 
tough legislation before the end of the year for new laws that would include 
requiring all firearms to be registered. 
</P>
<P>
 Justice Minister Allan Rock told reporters after meeting with gun owners and 
gun-control lobbyists in Montreal that he hopes to present proposals to 
Parliament in Ottawa before Christmas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
