RABBI SHLOMO CARLEBACH; SINGER, COMPOSER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rabbi Shlomo Carlebach, 69, the world-famous "singing rabbi" who performed on 
30 albums of Hasidic music. He rose to fame three decades ago as a storyteller, 
singer and composer of melodies known as "negunim" that became standards at 
Jewish services and weddings.Carlebach took over Congregation Kehilath Jacob in 
