<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOT EVERYONE ADORES THE RABBITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The article "Senior Citizens Decry Poisoning of Rabbits," (Oct. 20) makes it 
sound as if most of the Leisure World residents are in favor of the cottontail 
rabbits that infest our community. 
</P>
<P>
 However, 300 petitions represent less than 2% of our population.It's another 
example of the vocal minority getting all the attention. 
</P>
<P>
 Several months ago we were literally overrun by rabbits. On one particular 
lawn you could count four of them every evening. There were another three 
around and about my house. 
</P>
<P>
 In the mornings I had to gingerly step through and around their overnight 
droppings to pick up my copy of The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 As an environmentally correct solution, I obtained Leisure World gate passes 
for two coyotes who appear to be correcting the problem by providing the 
necessary ecological balance. 
</P>
<P>
 RUDY DOMENIE 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 
