<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARENTS' OPINIONS ARE HIGHLY VALUED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am a candidate for the Huntington Beach Union High School District Governing 
Board. An article "PTA Surveys Candidates in 22 School District Races (Oct. 
24)," misquoted me in a particularly serious way.The misquote, in the context 
it was presented, leads the reader to think that I have chosen a childless 
lifestyle, don't respect parental opinions, and may have some hidden agenda for 
running for school board. 
</P>
<P>
 None of this is true. In fact, the indirect quote is the exact opposite of my 
stated situation. That is, I am childless through circumstances beyond my 
control -- not my choice. 
</P>
<P>
 This quote was in response to a bluntly phrased question: What schools do your 
children attend, or did they attend if they are out of school? Anyone who knows 
me, knows that my status as a single person is a great regret in my life. 
</P>
<P>
 Furthermore, parental involvement in the schools system in one of my campaign 
issues. I am in favor of much more respect for parents than we currently have. 
</P>
<P>
 My answer, when read in its entirety, states that I believe parental 
involvement "is highly desired at all levels" within the system, but I also 
believe that the broader community needs and deserves a voice. 
</P>
<P>
 JOSEPH J. WAGNER 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
