<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELECTION MUST NOT SAP LAGUNA'S SPIRITO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Does Laguna still have a unique spirit? 
</P>
<P>
 The upcoming election is tearing the town apart. Some say it's a simple matter 
of pro-development people against anti-development people. 
</P>
<P>
 Are we as townspeople becoming morose, narcissistic and greedy, as some 
anthropologists say America has already become, or are we willing to commit 
ourselves to Laguna as a unique place with a unique spirit? 
