<P>
REFRESHING DEBATE IN BEILENSON-SYBERT RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Congratulations to John Schwada for a most accurate story on the first debate 
between Rep. Anthony Beilenson and his opponent, Richard Sybert ("Beilenson 
Backs Democrats in Debate with GOP's Rich Sybert," Oct. 12). 
</P>
<P>
 I was present Tuesday morning when they spoke to us seniors.It was most 
refreshing to hear Rep. Beilenson speak about all the accomplishments of the 
present Administration and not deride Mr. Sybert. I am sick and tired of all 
the berating that people running for office do against one another. Please tell 
us voters what you intend to accomplish should you be voted into office. Do not 
knock the other fellow; that is hitting below the belt, particularly when it 
may be false and a half-truth. 
</P>
<P>
 We want to know what your intentions are in making the United States a better 
place. We want to know what plans you have formulated. We want to know your 
qualifications. We want to know all about you, and not your opponent's failings 
as you see them. As responsible voters we will weigh the pros and cons. At 
least that is what I do. 
</P>
<P>
 MIRIAM B. MASON 
</P>
