<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN FOUND DEAD NEAR RINCON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Sheriff's Department is investigating the possible homicide 
of a woman found dead on a desolate road near the Rincon on Saturday evening. 
</P>
<P>
 The identity of the woman, who officials said is in her mid-20s, is being 
withheld pending notification of her next of kin. 
</P>
<P>
 The body was discovered by a passing motorist near Mussel Shoals at the end of 
a dead-end road, which runs parallel to the Ventura Freeway, shortly before 6 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 As the body of the woman, who appeared to be white with reddish brown hair, 
lay face up in the dirt, homicide detectives searched the scene for evidence. 
She was wearing a T-shirt, blue jeans and sneakers. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have not ruled out homicide, murder or even accidental death," said 
Sheriff's Lt. Larry Robertson. "There's even the possibility of a single 
gunshot wound." 
</P>
<P>
 The woman appeared to have suffered a severe blow to the head, Robertson said. 
Police had not determined how long the body had been there. 
</P>
