<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP; JOHNSON LEADS NORTH CAROLINA OVER N.C. STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leon Johnson rushed for 133 yards in 21 carries and scored three first-half 
touchdowns against North Carolina State's fourth-ranked defense as No. 24 North 
Carolina dominated the Wolfpack, 31-17, in an Atlantic Coast Conference game 
Saturday at Chapel Hill, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson scored on a three-yard run and on pass plays of 21 and 11 yards from 
Jason Stanicek as the Tar Heels, 6-2 overall and 3-2 in the ACC, rebounded from 
last weekend's 34-10 loss to No. 18 Virginia. The Wolfpack (5-2, 3-1) was 
limited to 60 yards in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Milanovich completed 25 of 35 passes for 291 yards and three touchdowns 
and Maryland's defense frustrated three Tulane quarterbacks in a 38-10 
nonconference victory at College Park, Md. Maryland (4-4) hasn't been at .500 
or better after eight games since 1990. Tulane (1-7) has lost its last two 
games by a combined 72 points. . . . Clemson's Louis Solomon ran for 159 yards 
and a touchdown and passed for one as the Tigers (3-5, 2-4) broke a three-game 
losing streak with a 24-8 ACC victory over Wake Forest (2-7, 0-6) at Clemson, 
S.C. EAST 
</P>
<P>
 Penn (6-0, 4-0) extended its Division I-AA winning streak to 18 games with a 
14-6 Ivy League victory over Yale (3-4, 1-3) at Philadelphia. . . . Cornell 
(6-1, 3-1) had five turnovers and lost, 16-3, to Brown (4-3, 1-3) in an Ivy 
League game at Ithaca, N.Y. . . . Vin Ferrara, completing 16 consecutive passes 
in one stretch, passed for 302 yards and three touchdowns as Harvard (4-3, 2-2) 
recorded a 35-12 Ivy League victory over Dartmouth (3-4, 1-3) at Hanover, N.H. 
. . . Marcellus Wiley ran for a touchdown and then made a key fumble recovery 
in the fourth quarter as Columbia (4-2-1) notched a 17-10 Ivy League victory 
over Princeton (5-2, 2-2) at New York. SOUTH 
</P>
<P>
 Louisville (5-3) took the opening kickoff and drove 65 yards on nine running 
plays for the game's only touchdown in a 10-6 victory over Memphis (5-3) at 
Louisville, Ky. . . . Marcus Crandell passed for two touchdowns and ran for one 
as East Carolina (5-3) went on a third-quarter spree and cruised to a 35-21 
victory over Cincinnati (0-7-1) at Greenville, N.C. . . . Redshirt freshman 
Heath Graham passed for 195 yards to lead Southern Mississippi (5-4) to a 47-29 
victory over Tulsa (2-6) at Hattiesburg, Miss. WEST 
</P>
<P>
 Craig Whelihan passed for 305 yards and four touchdowns to lead Pacific (5-3, 
3-1) to a 28-6 Big West victory over Utah State (2-6, 1-3) at Stockton. The 
Tigers are one victory shy of their first winning season since 1977. . . . 
Nevada Las Vegas (5-3, 4-0) notched a 23-10 Big West victory over San Jose 
State (1-7, 1-2) at Las Vegas. 
</P>
