<HEADLINE>
<P>
OLAJUWON TOO MUCH FOR CLIPPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Clippers did their best against Hakeem Olajuwon in the first half Saturday 
night, holding him to four points.Olajuwon, however, scored 17 of his 21 points 
in the second half to lead the Houston Rockets to a 111-103 exhibition victory 
in front of 21,268 at the Sports Palace. 
</P>
<P>
 The Clippers led, 57-47, at halftime before Olajuwon rallied the Rockets. 
</P>
<P>
 The Clippers took their last lead when Malik Sealy, who had a game-high 22 
points, hit a three-point shot with seven minutes to play to put the Clippers 
ahead, 92-91. A basket by Olajuwon then put the Rockets ahead for good, 93-92. 
</P>
<P>
 Elmore Spencer had 14 points and Tony Masssenburg 12 for the Clippers. 
</P>
