<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; IRVINE'S YABA FINISHES SECOND IN BIG WEST MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Jo Jo Yaba took second place, finishing the 3.1-mile course in 18 
minutes 36 seconds, one second behind Nevada's Rochelle Hair, to lead the 
Anteaters to a second-place finish in the Big West Conference cross-country 
championships Saturday in Logan, Utah. 
</P>
<P>
 Laura Monson finished fifth for Irvine in 18:51. Cal State Fullerton, which 
took fourth place behind Utah State, was led by Heather Killeen's fourth-place 
finish (18:45) and Teresa Santana's sixth place (18:56). 
</P>
<P>
 Favorite UC Santa Barbara captured the team title. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State finished seventh, led by Christa Ayuso's 13th-place finish 
(19:11). 
</P>
<P>
 On the men's side, Utah State's Mike Davidson took first place, finishing the 
five-mile course in 25:07, to lead the Aggies to the conference championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine's Bryan Contreras finished fifth (25:34), helping the Anteaters take 
third place in the team standings behind UC Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton's Mark Sinderson was sixth (25:44), leading the Titans to 
a fourth-place finish. Long Beach State, led by Pat Bendzick's 18th-place 
showing, was fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Hair was named the women's athlete of the year and Davidson earned the honor 
on the men's side. 
</P>
<P>
 In the UNLV Rebel Invitational men's soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Sacramento 2, UC Irvine 1 -- Bret Cowan's second-half goal was not 
enough for the Anteaters (11-7). Brandon Cavitt and Jamel Mitchell scored for 
Cal State Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Golden State Athletic Conference: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 2, Concordia 0 -- Jesus Miramontes, a former Sunny 
Hills player, and Peter Schumerth, who played for Esperanza, each scored a goal 
for Southern California College (7-11-1, 3-6). Bonner Rinn had eight saves for 
Concordia (4-13-1, 0-9). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 4, Cal State San Bernardino 2 -- Dana Mariotti scored two 
goals and Amber Thompson and Erin Rico each added one to lead host Cal State 
Fullerton (5-7-2). The victory stopped the Titans' winning streak at two games. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Traci Dahl had nine kills and 
Nichelle Burton had eight for Long Beach State (17-3, 12-1) in a 15-2, 15-1, 
15-5 victory. Lisi Fa'agata had seven kills for the Titans, who dropped to 
0-22, 0-11. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara 3, UC Irvine 0 -- Popi Edwards had nine kills and five digs 
for UC Irvine, which lost, 9-15, 4-15, 4-15. The Anteaters fell to 6-16, 5-10. 
UC Santa Barbara is 20-4, 9-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 3, Biola 2 -- Janine Katter had 21 kills and 
Angela Tonavanik added 18 to lead visiting Southern California College past 
Biola, 11-15, 15-2, 15-6, 15-17, 15-7. The Vanguards (17-9, 6-7) clinched at 
least an at-large playoff spot for the second consecutive year. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 3, Whittier 0 -- Shawna Parkinson had 17 kills and Lori Fuller added 
13 to lead Chapman (22-7) to a 15-13, 15-3, 15-4 victory at home. 
</P>
