<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other Mission Conference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 42, Northwestern 38 -- Jeff Clayton's 10-yard touchdown run with 
5:10 remaining in the fourth quarter gave Orange Coast its first victory of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates (1-6, 1-2) outgained Southwestern, 460-444, in total yards, 
dropping Southwestern to 0-6-1, 0-2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Jackson got the Pirates on the board, trailing, 14-0, in the first 
quarter. Jackson caught a 29-yard scoring pass from quarterback Matt Sauk to 
cut the deficit to 14-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast fell behind, 28-7, before Jackson caught his second touchdown 
pass of the game, a 14-yard score from Sauk. The Pirates trailed, 28-13, at 
halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 After Clayton's one-yard scoring run cut the lead to 28-21 in the third 
quarter, Sauk connected on his third touchdown of the game, a 22-yard pass to 
Jackson. The failed extra point conversion left the Pirates trailing by one, 
28-27. 
</P>
<P>
 Southwestern scored the next 10 points, increasing the lead to 38-27 in the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Sauk led Orange Coast back again, scoring on a one-yard run. The two-point 
conversion pulled the Pirates to within 38-35, setting up Clayton's final 
touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Clayton led the Pirates with 180 yards in 26 carries. Sauk completed 12 of 21 
passes for 230 yards. Jackson caught five passes for 142 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 25, Riverside 23 -- Shad Hinchen ran a kickoff back 100 yards for a 
touchdown and had an 80-yard punt return to lead Saddleback to it's first 
victory of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback, which was celebrating it's homecoming, held off a late rally from 
Riverside, which scored the last nine points of the game but failed on a 
two-point conversion when Anthony Richardson was stopped by linebackers Andy 
Osborne and Jeff Fackrell at the one-yard line. 
</P>
