<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 30, Pasadena 21 -- The Dons (6-1) extended their winning 
streak to six consecutive in a Mission Conference game at the Santa Ana Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 The key play of the game came in the third quarter with the Dons leading, 
10-6.After the Lancers (2-4-1) intercepted a Simon Fuentes pass on their 
39-yard line, they moved the ball to Rancho Santiago's 20-yard line. But then 
quarterback Joe Phears' pass was intercepted by linebacker Mike Fulton, who 
returned it 40 yards to Pasadena's 35-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 With the momentum on their side, the Dons moved the ball to the nine-yard line 
where Fuentes connected with wide receiver Jon Daniels in the corner of the end 
zone to put Rancho Santiago up, 17-6, with 22 seconds left in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Don defense came up strong on the next series, forcing a Lancer punt. 
After a 39-yard punt return by Roy Mendoza, the Dons gained 24 yards in two 
plays, capped off by a Ernest Wilson six-yard touchdown run with 13:45 
remaining in the game to take a 24-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson finished the game with 109 yards on 12 carries and two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive back James Stewart halted another Lancer drive with an interception 
and 45 yard return to the Pasadena five-yard line. Three plays later, Kevin 
Pola scored on a one-yard run, giving the Dons a 30-6 lead with 10:55 left in 
the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena was able to score two late touchdowns on long passes. Phears 
connected with Gavin Peries on a 49-yard touchdown with 7:03 left, and 46-yards 
scoring pass to Z Hodges with 1:38 remaining. Phears finished the game 
completing 23 of 46 passes for 318 yards. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
