<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Also in the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos Valley Christian 26, Whittier Christian 20 (tie-breaker) -- After 
Valley Christian quarterback Kirk Saarloos dashed 10 yards into the end zone to 
take a 6-0 lead in the tie-breaker, Jonathon De Bie intercepted a Garrett 
Estabrook pass to clinch a victory for the Crusaders at Whittier College. 
</P>
<P>
 The tie-breaker came as a result of a 20-yard touchdown pass to Keith Van 
Essen from Saarloos with 36 seconds left to play to tie the score, 20-20. 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian (5-3, 1-2) dominated most of the game, scoring on a 60-yard 
run by Jimmy Cuccia and a two-yard run by Nick Valdez. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley Christian's only first-half score came on a five-yard touchdown run by 
Jason Wilkinson, set up by Mike Cunningham's 85-yard kickoff return. 
</P>
<P>
 The Heralds took a 20-7 lead when Valdez scored on a 27-yard run with 5:23 
left to play. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crusaders (7-1, 3-0) bounced back with a nine-yard touchdown run by 
Cunningham two minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
 Three penalties forced the Heralds to punt and a 28-yard return by Cunningham 
brought Valley Christian to Whittier Christian's 31-yard line. The return set 
up Saarloos' pass to Van Essen five plays later. JASON HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
