<TEXT>
<P>
 A 1 1/2-year-old boy was in critical condition Saturday after being hit by a 
car while playing in a neighbor's driveway. 
</P>
<P>
 The neighbor was apparently backing away from the garage on Regalo Drive about 
9:30 a.m. when Matthew Zona was struck, said Lt. Rex Hatch of the Orange County 
Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Hatch said the driver apparently was not aware that the toddler had been hit 
and continued away from the home without stopping. The child suffered head 
injuries and was taken to Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center, where he 
was admitted to the pediatric intensive care unit. 
</P>
