<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLAN TO KILL 30 DEER AT ZOO TRIGGERS UPROAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A plan to kill 30 deer to cut costs at the local zoo threw this city into an 
uproar Saturday as noisy demonstrators, shouting "Save Bambi!," vowed to 
impeach the government. 
</P>
<P>
 Pickets lined the street leading to Mohegan Park Zoo while others demonstrated 
at City Hall -- even though it was closed for the day. 
</P>
<P>
 "One caller said: 'Kill the commission, keep the deer,' " said Mary Elizabeth 
Kenyon, secretary to the city manager. "That pretty well sums up the mood." 
</P>
<P>
 Because of fears that the herd could contract rabies or tuberculosis and then 
infect zoo visitors, zoo officials considered an elaborate plan of building 
fences and annually testing the herd. But costs for the program were so high 
that city officials decided to kill the herd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
