<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EAST LOS ANGELES; CABLE SHOWS PLAN TURKEY GIVEAWAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The staffs of two cable television shows will combine their efforts this year 
to raise money for a Thanksgiving turkey giveaway that they hope will feed 100 
families. 
</P>
<P>
 The shows, "East L.A. After Dark" and "Cruising With La Raza," both on 
Buenavision Community Access Cable, will hold a fund-raiser from 9 p.m. to 1 
a.m. on Nov. 12 at Tequila's Bar and Grill, 5226 E. Pomona Blvd., with comedian 
Diane Rodriguez and music by The Q Band.The turkey giveaway will be from 10 
a.m. to noon Nov. 19 for the first families arriving at Tequila's. 
</P>
<P>
 "East L.A. After Dark" delivered 30 turkeys and food baskets last year, but 
this year the staffs of the shows decided that a combined effort would reach 
more families, said Dolores Guerrero-cruz, producer of "East L.A. After Dark." 
</P>
<P>
 The turkey baskets include all the trimmings, including pies. 
</P>
<P>
 In its sixth year of production, "East L.A. After Dark" features politicians, 
students and people from the community -- including the neighborhood Little 
League team -- speaking about what's important to them. 
</P>
<P>
 "Cruising With La Raza" debuted in 1990 and focuses on East Los Angeles and 
Southern California car clubs and events. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $5. The event will include food and door prizes such as T-shirts, 
books, CDs and art. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 722-7992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
