COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: HYDE PARK; CARTOONIST TO HOST HALLOWEEN EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Comic book artist David G. Brown will host an afternoon of Halloween 
activities for children at the Hyde Park Public Library on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 An artist and cartoonist who created the comic book series "L.A. Phoenix" in 
the wake of the 1992 riots, Brown will teach participants how to decorate 
trick-or-treat bags and will demonstrate how to draw monsters. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, whose series features a super-hero who literally rose from the ashes of 
burned buildings to stop crime and urge people to live together harmoniously, 
teaches a comic art workshop at Watts Tower Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event will be at the library, 6527 Crenshaw Blvd., from 4 to 6 p.m. 
Candy and other treats will be distributed. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 750-7241. 
