<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: HUNTINGTON PARK; CITY OFFERS HOUSING IMPROVEMENT 
LOANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Huntington Park is offering loans with little or no interest and 
rebates to qualified home and rental property owners for necessary property 
improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 Loans are available for roofing, plumbing, aluminum windows, outdoor stucco, 
electrical upgrades and additional room construction. 
</P>
<P>
 Homeowners can obtain up to $25,000 in loans and/or up to 50% reimbursement 
for a maximum of $4,000 in rebates. Rental property owners can obtain up to 
$20,000 per unit (not to exceed $120,000) in loans. 
</P>
<P>
 All funds are available on a first-come, first-served basis from the 
Residential Rehabilitation Program and are administered by the Community 
Development Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 582-6161. 
</P>
