<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EAST LOS ANGELES; HOUSING OPENS FOR DISABLED HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Community Rehabilitation Services Inc. officially opened a home Thursday that 
will serve eight homeless and disabled people. 
</P>
<P>
 The house, at 3551 E. 4th St., is the only such facility on the Eastside that 
offers low rent as well as services for the disabled, according to members of 
Community Rehabilitation Services. 
</P>
<P>
 Community Rehabilitation Services, which has served the disabled for 16 years, 
provides job training, counseling and education. It will offer the residents 
similar services during their two-year stay at the home so they can become 
independent, said board President Al Rivera.  
</P>
<P>
 Many of the residents will hold jobs or obtain them during their stay, Rivera 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 266-0453. 
