<HEADLINE>
<P>
DECISION '94 / SPECIAL GUIDE TO CALIFORNIA'S ELECTIONS; FINDING A CURE IN A 
YEAR OF ANGER; ABOUT THIS SECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Nov. 8 Californians will choose a governor, a U.S. senator and seven other 
statewide officeholders. They will decide on Proposition 187, the anti-illegal 
immigration initiative, and other controversial measures. Today, The Times 
offers this special guide to California's elections, with reports on the 
candidates and issues in all of these races. Congressional and state 
legislative contests and local elections are being covered in daily and 
suburban sections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
